<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 16. Curarea crassa pistillate plant: A fruiting branch B innermost sepal, adaxial surface C petal, abaxial surface D carpels (based on Jardim et al. 609)." , "Figure 25. Geographic distribution of Curarea tomentocarpa and C. toxicofera." , "Figure 27. Curarea toxicofera pistillate plant: A flowering branch B flower bud C innermost sepal, adaxial surface D petals and carpels E petal abaxial surface F infructescence (A-E based on Gentry et al. 21624 F based on Revilla et al. 2566)." , "Figure 15. Curarea crassa staminate plant: A flowering branch B detail of inflorescence C flower bud D inner sepal, adaxial surface E-F outer and inner petals, abaxial views G-H outer stamens, abaxial-lateral surfaces (based on Thomas et al. 10900)." , "Figure 2. Transversal sections of stem of Curarea: A relatively round stem of C. aff. tomentocarpa (Ortiz 197), showing wide rays B flattened stem of C. tecunarum (Ortiz & Vasquez 214) showing successive partial rings. Scale bar: 0.5 cm (A); 1.7 cm (B)." , "Figure 26. Curarea toxicofera staminate plant: A flowering branch B detail of inflorescence C flower bud D inner sepal, adaxial surface E-F outer and inner petals, abaxial and latero-adaxial surfaces G-H outer stamens, lateral and abaxial surfaces (A-B based on Ule 5631 C-H based on Encarnacion 1094)." , "Figure 1. Schematic representation of affinities and drupelet: A phylogenetic affinities of Curarea and related taxa, modified from Ortiz et al. 2016, three asterisks (***) indicate 100 % support in all analyses in the referred study B schematic illustration of a Curarea drupelet showing the length and width planes measured, ca. / abbrev> = carpophore, frpe = fruiting pedicel, rs = remnant of style." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/211313" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/211324" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/211322" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/211298" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/211312" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/211299" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/211325" .

